h1. ACME Certificate Enrollment Testing - OpenBao PKI Lab

{panel:title=Test Metadata|borderStyle=solid|borderColor=#ccc|titleBGColor=#e8f5e9|bgColor=#f1f8e9}
*Test Date:* February 7, 2026, 01:45 CET
*Test Domain:* {{testserver.solar.energy.internal}}
*Infrastructure:* OpenBao v2.5.0 (Kubernetes/Kind)
*Test Objective:* Validate ACME protocol implementation for automated certificate enrollment
{panel}

----

h2. Executive Summary

This document provides comprehensive evidence of ACME (Automatic Certificate Management Environment) protocol testing against the OpenBao PKI infrastructure. The testing validates that the PKI can automatically issue certificates to clients using the industry-standard ACME protocol.

{info:title=Test Outcome}
✅ *ACME Protocol:* Fully functional and tested
✅ *OpenBao PKI:* Root and Intermediate CA properly configured
✅ *Test Methodology:* Protocol validation via Python client
✅ *Endpoint Accessibility:* All ACME endpoints responding correctly
{info}

----

