h3. ACME Protocol Flow

The ACME protocol follows a standardized 6-step process:

{panel:title=ACME Workflow Sequence|borderStyle=solid|borderColor=#1565c0|titleBGColor=#e3f2fd}
# *Directory Discovery* → Client retrieves ACME endpoints
# *Nonce Generation* → Anti-replay protection mechanism
# *Account Registration* → Client registers with CA
# *Certificate Order* → Client requests certificate for domain
# *Challenge Authorization* → CA validates domain ownership
# *Finalization & Download* → CA issues and client downloads certificate
{panel}

