h3. 5. ACME Role Configuration

*Role Name:* {{acme-default}}

|| Parameter || Value || Description ||
| allowed_domains | {{[*]}} | Wildcard - accepts any domain |
| allow_subdomains | {{true}} | Subdomains permitted |
| allow_any_name | {{true}} | No domain restrictions |
| max_ttl | {{720h}} (30 days) | Maximum certificate lifetime |
| client_flag | {{true}} | TLS Client Authentication enabled |
| server_flag | {{true}} | TLS Server Authentication enabled |
| key_type | {{rsa}} | RSA key algorithm |
| key_bits | {{2048}} | 2048-bit RSA keys |
| key_usage | DigitalSignature, KeyAgreement, KeyEncipherment | Standard usage extensions |

{note:title=Security Configuration}
This is a *permissive lab configuration*. Production environments should restrict:
* {{allowed_domains}} to specific organizational domains
* {{max_ttl}} according to security policy
* Enable {{enforce_hostnames}} for strict validation
{note}

