h2. ACME Challenge Validation Details

h3. Supported Challenge Types

{panel:title=http-01 Challenge|borderColor=#0288d1|titleBGColor=#b3e5fc}
*Mechanism:* HTTP file serving
*Validation:* CA retrieves {{http://<domain>/.well-known/acme-challenge/<token>}}
*Use Case:* Web servers with HTTP access
*Status:* ✅ Supported by OpenBao
{panel}

{panel:title=dns-01 Challenge|borderColor=#0288d1|titleBGColor=#b3e5fc}
*Mechanism:* DNS TXT record
*Validation:* CA queries {{_acme-challenge.<domain>}} DNS TXT record
*Use Case:* Wildcard certificates, servers without HTTP
*Status:* ✅ Supported by OpenBao
{panel}

{panel:title=tls-alpn-01 Challenge|borderColor=#0288d1|titleBGColor=#b3e5fc}
*Mechanism:* TLS certificate with ALPN extension
*Validation:* CA connects via TLS on port 443
*Use Case:* Pure TLS servers
*Status:* ✅ Supported by OpenBao
{panel}

h3. Network Validation Architecture

{code:title=Challenge Validation Flow}
┌──────────────────────┐
│  ACME Client         │
│  (Certbot/Cert-Mgr)  │
└──────────┬───────────┘
           │ 1. Request Certificate
           │    (POST /acme/new-order)
           ↓
┌──────────────────────┐
│  OpenBao ACME Server │
│  (pki_int)           │
└──────────┬───────────┘
           │ 2. Respond with Challenge
           │    (http-01, dns-01, etc.)
           ↓
┌──────────────────────┐
│  ACME Client         │
│  Provisions Challenge│
│  - HTTP file         │
│  - DNS TXT record    │
└──────────┬───────────┘
           │ 3. Notify Ready
           │    (POST /acme/challenge/<id>)
           ↓
┌──────────────────────┐
│  OpenBao ACME Server │
│  Validates Challenge │
│  - HTTP GET          │
│  - DNS query         │
└──────────┬───────────┘
           │ 4. Issue Certificate
           │    (if validation succeeds)
           ↓
┌──────────────────────┐
│  ACME Client         │
│  Download Certificate│
└──────────────────────┘
{code}

{warning:title=Network Limitation Identified}
During testing, we identified that the OpenBao pod (running in Kubernetes) cannot directly reach services on the host machine's {{localhost (127.0.0.1)}} for http-01 challenge validation.

*Workaround Options:*
# Deploy test servers inside the Kubernetes cluster
# Use host's LAN IP with services like {{nip.io}} for DNS resolution
# Use dns-01 challenges (no HTTP connectivity required)
{warning}

